\subsection{Displaying the prompt}
\label{sec:display-prompt}

%claude:
In [[rc]], the [[$prompt]] variable is a two-element list:
the first element is the {\em main prompt} (e.g., [["% "]]),
and the second element is the {\em continuation prompt} displayed
when a command spans multiple lines (e.g., [["\t"]]).
%
The prompt is printed
% lazily
by the input layer, just before it
reads the next character---not by the command-execution code when a
command finishes (You do still see the prompt after each command, but only
because the shell then loops back to read the next line.).
%
The mechanism is the global [[doprompt]] flag, set to [[true]] after each
newline (or EOF) and reset to [[false]] once the prompt has been printed.

<<global [[doprompt]]>>=
bool doprompt = true;
@
% set to true by default! so first time run rc, will get a prompt.

<<global [[promptstr]]>>=
