\section{Quoted strings ([['...']])}
\label{sec:quoting}

%claude:
In [[rc]], strings are quoted with single quotes.
To include a literal single quote inside a quoted string,
you double it: [['it''s']] produces [[it's]].
%
The [<inquote>] flag is needed by [<getnext()>] because
inside a quoted string, backslash-newline should {\em not}
be treated as a line continuation.
%
The [<lastword>] flag tracks whether the previous token
was a word, which the grammar uses to decide whether
adjacent tokens should be concatenated.
% (e.g., [[a^b]]).

<<global [[inquote]]>>=
bool inquote;
@
