%claude:
Function definition in [[rc]] is written as \verb+fn name {body}+.
The second form, [[fn name]] without a body, {\em deletes}
the function definition.
%
Note that [[words]] (not just a single word) is accepted below
as the function name: this allows defining a function
for multiple names at once (e.g., \verb+fn sigint sighup {...}+
to handle multiple signals with the same handler).

<<cmd rule other cases>>=
|   FN words brace  {$$=tree2(FN, $2, $3);}
|   FN words        {$$=tree1(FN, $2);}
