\section{Lists ([[(...)]])}

%claude:
In [[rc]], parentheses create lists: [[(a b c)]] is a list
of three words. This is how you assign multiple values
to a variable: [[x=(a b c)]].
Lists are first-class values in [[rc]], which is one of its main
improvements over the Bourne shell.

<<comword rule other cases>>=
|   '(' words ')'   {$$=tree1(PAREN, $2);}
@


